Michael Bissex (born 28 September 1944 in Newbridge, Bath) is a former English first-class cricketer. He played with Gloucestershire County Cricket Club for his entire career.
In 1966-67 he toured Pakistan with the MCC Under-25 side, and in 1968 he represented England's Under-25 side.
